% Children who can do division
Cohorts of children in Std IV in 2008, 2010 and 2012

<!-- Bar chart image -->

This graph shows the progress of three cohorts from Std IV to Std VIII. For example, the first cohort was in Std IV in 2008, in Std VI in 2010, and in Std VIII in 2012. For this cohort: % children who were at division level in Std IV (in 2008) was 27.5%, and in Std VI (in 2010) was 55%. When the cohort reached Std VIII in 2012, this figure was 44.3%. The progress of each of these cohorts can be understood in the same way.


